                  <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                  <p>This folder consists of records documenting the building of Connecticut Hall. The records include documentation of workers who constructed the building, including Jethro Luke and his son Gad Luke, both free Black men living in New Haven, and by five enslaved Black men - Dick, Mingo, Jack, and two others whose names were not recorded.</p>
